China had 582,000 community healthcare workers as of the end of 2018, a 5.1-percent increase from the previous year, according to the National Health Commission. The country had 9,352 community health centers by the end of 2018, an increase of 205 from a year ago, the commission said in its statistical report on development of the nation's medical and healthcare sector in 2018. These centers received 640 million visits by out-patients and 3.4 million in-patients, both up from 2017, the report says. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star